    "FermionBasis[c1, c2, ..., n] returns a basis for the system of fermions \
{c1, c2, ...} each element of which contains up to n particles. \
FermionBasis[c1, c2, ..., {n}] returns a basis of fermions {c1, c2, ...} each \
element of which contains exactly n particles. FermionBasis[c1, c2, ..., {m, \
n}] returns a basis of fermions {c1, c2, ...} each element of which contains \
from m to n particles. FermionBasis[{c1, c2, ...}, opts] returns the \
many-particle basis for fermions c1, c2, ... in a structured form of the \
occupation-number representation. FermionBasis[c, spec] is equivalent to \
FermionBasis[{c}, spec].", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
